EXTRACTED VALUE: Its predecessor had better scares, pace and atmosphere. In short, it was better. [Jan 2008, p.96]
Entertaining enough at first, but lacking any staying power. [Apr 2008, p.78]
It ticks all the boxes for those fans though, with only the slightly underwhelming visuals likely to disappoint.
The game reminded me very much of Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles (which did not go down well with this particular reviewer at the time, or now even).
NFS Prostreet is a highly polished title, but completely absent of entertainment value.
